description: In protected area at mouth of harbor. several mothers with baby, resting, watched babies nursing, several mothers caught large clams and shared with baby.

project.title: Parental Care
project.description: Most people think of birds, mammals, or maybe fish when parental care is mentioned, but parents of a huge variety of animals provide protection, food or some other form of care to their offspring. Whether it's the harvestman pictured in this project icon guarding developing embryos, or a dendrobatid frog carrying their tadpole to a new bromeliad, parental care is ubiquitous. Please help us document this fascinating life history strategy by adding your photos of adults with young, on nests, etc. Note, it is not always easy to tell whether parental care is being observed, but please consider adding your photo even if you're not sure as it will serve to stimulate discussion.

taxon.name: Enhydra lutris
taxon.wikipedia_summary: The sea otter (Enhydra lutris) is a marine mammal native to the coasts of the northern and eastern North Pacific Ocean. Adult sea otters typically weigh between 14 and 45 kg (31 and 99 lb), making them the heaviest members of the weasel family, but among the smallest marine mammals. Unlike most marine mammals, the sea otter's primary form of insulation is an exceptionally thick coat of fur, the densest in the animal kingdom. Although it can walk...
